# Comment Guidelines

## Avoid Generic AI-like Comments
❌ **Don't use these:**
- `/* Padding untuk konsistensi dengan header */`
- `/* Lebih kecil lagi untuk small mobile */`
- `/* Memberikan space untuk header */`
- `/* Space untuk notification button */`
- `/* Dark theme adjustments */`
- `/* Mobile devices */`
- `/* Sign In Button Variants */`
- `/* Animation for smooth transitions */`
- `/* Ensure proper spacing */`
- `/* Handle responsive design */`

## Use Natural Professional Comments
✅ **Use these instead:**

### Complex Function Explanations
```scss
/* Conditional header layout based on authentication status */
/* Toast container with slide-in animation from right */
/* Button with loading state and spinner animation */
```

### Business Logic Explanations
```scss
/* Authenticated users: notification + profile */
/* Unauthenticated users: language + theme + sign in */
/* Responsive breakpoints for mobile optimization */
```

### Technical Implementation
```scss
/* Z-index stacking for modal overlay */
/* CSS Grid layout for dashboard cards */
/* Flexbox centering for button alignment */
```

### Component Architecture
```scss
/* Main navigation wrapper */
/* Form validation error states */
/* Loading skeleton animation */
```

## Guidelines
- Only comment when explaining complex logic or important architectural decisions
- Use natural, developer-like language
- Avoid obvious or redundant comments
- Focus on "why" not "what" when commenting
- Keep comments concise and meaningful
